{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777814351658,"sessionID":"ses_212054657ffeaYfN5kgzrKgi2w","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"tool_bash_lqc0WBJZQwK9C83HdAfM","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"cat << 'EOF' > parse_vcd3.py\ndef parse_vcd(filename):\n    vars = {}\n    values = {}\n    with open(filename, 'r') as f:\n        lines = f.readlines()\n        \n    for line in lines:\n        line = line.strip()\n        if line.startswith('$var'):\n            parts = line.split()\n            id = parts[3]\n            name = parts[4]\n            vars[id] = name\n            values[name] = {}\n        elif line.startswith('#'):\n            time = int(line[1:])\n        elif line.startswith('b'):\n            if ' ' in line:\n                val, id = line.split()\n                val = val[1:]\n                if id in vars:\n                    values[vars[id]][time] = val\n        elif line.startswith('0') or line.startswith('1'):\n            val = line[0]\n            id = line[1:]\n            if id in vars:\n                values[vars[id]][time] = val\n\n    return vars, values\n\nvars, values = parse_vcd('formal/riscv-formal/cores/bench/checks/reg_ch0/engine_0/trace.vcd')\n\ntimes = sorted(list(set(t for d in values.values() for t in d.keys())))\n\n# state tracking\nstate = {}\nfor t in times:\n    for sig in ['io_rvfi_valid_0', 'io_rvfi_order_0', 'io_rvfi_insn_0', 'io_rvfi_rd_addr_0', 'io_rvfi_rd_wdata_0', 'io_rvfi_rs1_addr_0', 'io_rvfi_rs1_rdata_0', 'io_rvfi_rs2_addr_0', 'io_rvfi_rs2_rdata_0']:\n        if t in values.get(sig, {}):\n            state[sig] = values[sig][t]\n            \n    if state.get('io_rvfi_valid_0') == '1':\n        print(f\"RETIRE: order={int(state.get('io_rvfi_order_0', '0'), 2)} insn={state.get('io_rvfi_insn_0')} rd={int(state.get('io_rvfi_rd_addr_0', '0'), 2)} wdata={state.get('io_rvfi_rd_wdata_0')} rs1={int(state.get('io_rvfi_rs1_addr_0', '0'), 2)} r1data={state.get('io_rvfi_rs1_rdata_0')} rs2={int(state.get('io_rvfi_rs2_addr_0', '0'), 2)} r2data={state.get('io_rvfi_rs2_rdata_0')}\")\n\nEOF\npython3 parse_vcd3.py","description":"Print order and rs2"},"output":"Traceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gemini-3_1-pro-rep1/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260503-001-r1s0/parse_vcd3.py\", line 31, in <module>\n    vars, values = parse_vcd('formal/riscv-formal/cores/bench/checks/reg_ch0/engine_0/trace.vcd')\n                   ~~~~~~~~~^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n  File \"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gemini-3_1-pro-rep1/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260503-001-r1s0/parse_vcd3.py\", line 4, in parse_vcd\n    with open(filename, 'r') as f:\n         ~~~~^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\nFileNotFoundError: [Errno 2] No such file or directory: 'formal/riscv-formal/cores/bench/checks/reg_ch0/engine_0/trace.vcd'\n","metadata":{"output":"Traceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gemini-3_1-pro-rep1/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260503-001-r1s0/parse_vcd3.py\", line 31, in <module>\n    vars, values = parse_vcd('formal/riscv-formal/cores/bench/checks/reg_ch0/engine_0/trace.vcd')\n                   ~~~~~~~~~^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n  File \"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gemini-3_1-pro-rep1/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260503-001-r1s0/parse_vcd3.py\", line 4, in parse_vcd\n    with open(filename, 'r') as f:\n         ~~~~^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\nFileNotFoundError: [Errno 2] No such file or directory: 'formal/riscv-formal/cores/bench/checks/reg_ch0/engine_0/trace.vcd'\n","exit":1,"description":"Print order and rs2","truncated":false},"title":"Print order and rs2","time":{"start":1777814351654,"end":1777814351657}},"metadata":{"openrouter":{"reasoning_details":[{"type":"reasoning.text","text":"**Analyzing Instruction Traces**\n\nI'm currently examining instruction traces to understand data flow. Specifically, I'm looking at the register `rd` at time 80, noting its value and the `wdata`. Then, I'm comparing that to the state at time 170, observing `rd`, `rs1`, and `rdata`.\n\n**Tracing Instruction Flow**\n\nI've confirmed the data flow for instruction at time 80 and 170, with `rd` and `rs1` values aligning as expected. The JAL instruction at time 130 also shows a perfect match for its `wdata`. However, a failure in `rvfi_reg_check` at `register_index` 22 prompts further investigation. I'm modifying the script to include instruction `order` in the output to pinpoint the exact instruction causing the discrepancy.\n\n","format":"google-gemini-v1","index":0},{"type":"reasoning.encrypted","data":"","id":"tool_bash_lqc0WBJZQwK9C83HdAfM","format":"google-gemini-v1","index":0}]}},"id":"prt_dedfe2f06001Yh1ALsa1sOcSz1","sessionID":"ses_212054657ffeaYfN5kgzrKgi2w","messageID":"msg_dedfdfe95001bDTWbwM6UTHWwJ"}}
