{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777814311575,"sessionID":"ses_21207aec8ffe3jzZK95BS8Kv96","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"tool_bash_xV0n8fiH9ZOP51QBuw1x","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"View formal checks config","command":"cat formal/checks.cfg","workdir":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gemini-3_1-pro-rep1/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260503-003-r1s2"},"output":"[options]\nisa rv32im\nnret 2\nsolver bitwuzla\n\n[depth]\n# BMC depth per check. 2nd column (where present) is the k-induction prove\n# depth. Keep depths matched to the current pipeline so bugs within ~20\n# cycles of any symbolic instruction stream are exposed.\ninsn          20\nreg       10  20\npc_fwd    10  20\npc_bwd    10  20\ncausal    10  20\n# unique   — no two retirements share rvfi_order (catches double-retire)\n# cover    — sanity that the CPU retires (prevents vacuous-pass suites)\n# ill      — illegal instructions must trap; rvfi_trap from decoder.is_illegal\n# liveness — CPU makes forward progress under any symbolic stream\nunique     1 10 20\ncover      1    20\nill             20\nliveness   1 10 20\n\n[defines]\n`define RISCV_FORMAL_ALIGNED_MEM\n# RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS — fast mode. Substitutes M-ext mul/div/rem with\n# simpler XOR-of-add/sub formulas so bitwuzla solves them inside the\n# 20-step BMC budget (rvfi.rst §7.6 \"Alternative arithmetic operations\").\n#\n# IMPORTANT — what this DOES and DOES NOT prove:\n#   ✓ proves: M-ext bypassing, operand routing (rs1/rs2 -> unit -> rd),\n#             stall/forwarding behavior on mul/div, all I-base arithmetic\n#             and trap discipline.\n#   ✗ does NOT prove: the actual MUL/DIV/REM arithmetic is correct.\n#     The DUT and the spec both implement the same XOR substitute under\n#     this define, so a wrong real multiplier can still pass formal here.\n#\n# M-extension arithmetic correctness is covered separately by:\n#   1. test/test_alu.py — 30+ vectors per M-ext op, exact bit results.\n#   2. cosim against test/cosim/reference.py — every retired MUL/DIV/REM\n#      diff'd field-by-field.\n#   3. `make formal-deep` — same checks without ALTOPS. SLOW (~hours per\n#      M-ext check) but proves real arithmetic. Run periodically, not in\n#      the per-iteration orchestrator loop.\n`define RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS\n\n[cover]\n# Sanity cover: the CPU must retire at least one non-trapping instruction.\n# A vacuous suite (nothing ever retires) would fail this — no symbolic\n# trace can make rvfi_valid && !rvfi_trap go true.\nalways @* if (!reset) cover (rvfi_valid && !rvfi_trap);\n\n[verilog-files]\n@basedir@/cores/@core@/core_pkg.sv\n@basedir@/cores/@core@/alu.sv\n@basedir@/cores/@core@/decoder.sv\n@basedir@/cores/@core@/imm_gen.sv\n@basedir@/cores/@core@/reg_file.sv\n@basedir@/cores/@core@/if_stage.sv\n@basedir@/cores/@core@/id_stage.sv\n@basedir@/cores/@core@/ex_stage.sv\n@basedir@/cores/@core@/mem_stage.sv\n@basedir@/cores/@core@/wb_stage.sv\n@basedir@/cores/@core@/hazard_unit.sv\n@basedir@/cores/@core@/forward_unit.sv\n@basedir@/cores/@core@/core.sv\n@basedir@/cores/@core@/wrapper.sv\n","metadata":{"output":"[options]\nisa rv32im\nnret 2\nsolver bitwuzla\n\n[depth]\n# BMC depth per check. 2nd column (where present) is the k-induction prove\n# depth. Keep depths matched to the current pipeline so bugs within ~20\n# cycles of any symbolic instruction stream are exposed.\ninsn          20\nreg       10  20\npc_fwd    10  20\npc_bwd    10  20\ncausal    10  20\n# unique   — no two retirements share rvfi_order (catches double-retire)\n# cover    — sanity that the CPU retires (prevents vacuous-pass suites)\n# ill      — illegal instructions must trap; rvfi_trap from decoder.is_illegal\n# liveness — CPU makes forward progress under any symbolic stream\nunique     1 10 20\ncover      1    20\nill             20\nliveness   1 10 20\n\n[defines]\n`define RISCV_FORMAL_ALIGNED_MEM\n# RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS — fast mode. Substitutes M-ext mul/div/rem with\n# simpler XOR-of-add/sub formulas so bitwuzla solves them inside the\n# 20-step BMC budget (rvfi.rst §7.6 \"Alternative arithmetic operations\").\n#\n# IMPORTANT — what this DOES and DOES NOT prove:\n#   ✓ proves: M-ext bypassing, operand routing (rs1/rs2 -> unit -> rd),\n#             stall/forwarding behavior on mul/div, all I-base arithmetic\n#             and trap discipline.\n#   ✗ does NOT prove: the actual MUL/DIV/REM arithmetic is correct.\n#     The DUT and the spec both implement the same XOR substitute under\n#     this define, so a wrong real multiplier can still pass formal here.\n#\n# M-extension arithmetic correctness is covered separately by:\n#   1. test/test_alu.py — 30+ vectors per M-ext op, exact bit results.\n#   2. cosim against test/cosim/reference.py — every retired MUL/DIV/REM\n#      diff'd field-by-field.\n#   3. `make formal-deep` — same checks without ALTOPS. SLOW (~hours per\n#      M-ext check) but proves real arithmetic. Run periodically, not in\n#      the per-iteration orchestrator loop.\n`define RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS\n\n[cover]\n# Sanity cover: the CPU must retire at least one non-trapping instruction.\n# A vacuous suite (nothing ever retires) would fail this — no symbolic\n# trace can make rvfi_valid && !rvfi_trap go true.\nalways @* if (!reset) cover (rvfi_valid && !rvfi_trap);\n\n[verilog-files]\n@basedir@/cores/@core@/core_pkg.sv\n@basedir@/cores/@core@/alu.sv\n@basedir@/cores/@core@/decoder.sv\n@basedir@/cores/@core@/imm_gen.sv\n@basedir@/cores/@core@/reg_file.sv\n@basedir@/cores/@core@/if_stage.sv\n@basedir@/cores/@core@/id_stage.sv\n@basedir@/cores/@core@/ex_stage.sv\n@basedir@/cores/@core@/mem_stage.sv\n@basedir@/cores/@core@/wb_stage.sv\n@basedir@/cores/@core@/hazard_unit.sv\n@basedir@/cores/@core@/forward_unit.sv\n@basedir@/cores/@core@/core.sv\n@basedir@/cores/@core@/wrapper.sv\n","exit":0,"description":"View formal checks config","truncated":false},"title":"View formal checks config","time":{"start":1777814311573,"end":1777814311575}},"metadata":{"openrouter":{"reasoning_details":[{"type":"reasoning.text","text":"**Locating Files**\n\nI'm currently searching for the specific files needed for riscv-formal. My focus is on pinpointing their exact location within the project structure.\n\n","format":"google-gemini-v1","index":0},{"type":"reasoning.encrypted","data":"CiYBjz1rX317FLQthDU8+oIvPVTTtEVJNU5drv5DVWgXG5c4fsChcQpLAY89a1+B1/UCFtPhgLAaACYnPbQHZ6nT3bFIpkHaSYuBhJFYJerjdKKTaXgXVqIV6yQIjqRjv7zjnhEpbGYtAEcY61sOYe+trGxU","id":"tool_bash_xV0n8fiH9ZOP51QBuw1x","format":"google-gemini-v1","index":0}]}},"id":"prt_dedfd9288001XH7EWlwhyY4rIg","sessionID":"ses_21207aec8ffe3jzZK95BS8Kv96","messageID":"msg_dedfd7fc40010HGUQqNO67eiXR"}}
